notesStmt.note: Title supplied by cataloger based on bookseller's description.

msContents.summary: Two volumes of recipes for elixirs, tinctures, pills, syrups, purgatives, and potions. At the beginning of the first volume is a table of pharmaceutical symbols (pp. 1-5). At the end of the second volume (8pp. following p. 105) is a record of accounts for the years 1803-1805, documenting sales to a convent.
msContents.textLang: Ingredients in Latin, instructions in German

supportDesc.extent: 2 v. (93, 57 leaves) : 331 x 209 mm. and 323 x 194 mm. both bound to 332 x 212 mm
supportDesc.foliation: V.1: Paper, 93; 1-137, 137-187; V.2: Paper, 57; 1-104, [x]; contemporary or near-contemporary pagination in ink, upper outer corners.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by what appears to be a single hand.

binding.p: Calf-backed paste-paper boards with ties (bookseller's description).

origin.p: Written in southern Germany [?], possibly Swabia or Bavaria, in the second half of the 18th century (bookseller's description).
